{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775861604051,"sessionID":"ses_28666708effe1Q09QT4ynjRvQv","part":{"id":"prt_d79999ecf001DMPgcxJYlkr1RX","messageID":"msg_d79999852001vVf59hqTv3z2fu","sessionID":"ses_28666708effe1Q09QT4ynjRvQv","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861619807,"sessionID":"ses_28666708effe1Q09QT4ynjRvQv","part":{"id":"prt_d7999dc3e001K5F5tlPlQftSZc","messageID":"msg_d79999852001vVf59hqTv3z2fu","sessionID":"ses_28666708effe1Q09QT4ynjRvQv","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-043bca18473f4b0685a5990fe550b8d5","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Proposal: AR-018 — Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement an idle cleanup controller in `pkg/agentd` to automatically detect and clean up idle or abandoned AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources in the agentcube system. This controller will help optimize resource utilization, prevent resource leaks, and maintain system health by removing resources that are no longer actively used.\n\nThe controller will monitor AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources, track their activity and lifecycle states, and perform cleanup actions based on configurable idle timeout policies.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In-Scope\n\n1. **Controller Implementation** (`pkg/agentd/controller/idle_cleanup.go`)\n   - Kubernetes controller implementing the reconciliation loop for idle resource detection\n   - Controller registration and lifecycle management\n   - Configuration for idle timeout thresholds\n   - Graceful shutdown handling\n\n2. **Idle Detection Logic**\n   - Monitor AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources using client-go informers\n   - Track last activity timestamp, status conditions, and lifecycle events\n   - Evaluate idle state based on configurable policies:\n     - No pod/execution activity for N minutes\n     - Completed/Failed status for N minutes\n     - Orphaned resources (no matching parent/owner references)\n\n3. **Cleanup Actions**\n   - Delete idle AgentRuntime resources\n   - Delete idle CodeInterpreter resources\n   - Event logging for audit and observability\n   - Optional notifications via Kubernetes events\n\n4. **Configuration**\n   - Command-line flags for idle timeout values\n   - Configurable label selectors for targeted cleanup\n   - Dry-run mode support for testing\n\n5. **Testing**\n   - Unit tests for idle detection logic\n   - Integration tests with fake clientset\n   - End-to-end tests with mocked Kubernetes API\n\n### Out-of-Scope\n\n- Garbage collection of dependent pods, PVCs, or other child resources (handled by Kubernetes garbage collector)\n- Metrics and monitoring integration (to be added in future AR)\n- Dynamic policy configuration via CRDs\n- Resource quota or limit enforcement\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Resource Utilization\n- **Positive**: Reduces idle resource consumption, frees up cluster capacity\n- **Minimal**: Controller runtime overhead is low (lightweight reconciliation)\n\n### System Reliability\n- **Positive**: Prevents resource exhaustion from accumulated idle resources\n- **Positive**: Reduces technical debt from abandoned workloads\n- **Risk**: Potential for premature deletion if timeouts are misconfigured (mitigated by conservative defaults and dry-run mode)\n\n### Operational Impact\n- **Positive**: Automated cleanup reduces manual intervention\n- **Positive**: Improved observability through event logging\n- **Neutral**: Adds one more controller to the agentd control plane (minimal resource footprint)\n\n### Dependencies\n- Uses existing `client-go` library for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter API access\n- Integrates with existing agentd controller framework and leader election\n- No changes required to CRD definitions or API server\n\n### User Experience\n- **Transparent**: Cleanup happens automatically without user action\n- **Configurable**: Operators can tune timeout values to match workload patterns\n- **Safe**: Dry-run mode allows validation before enabling actual deletions\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### 1. Manual Cleanup via kubectl\n- **Pros**: No controller overhead, complete control\n- **Cons**: High operational burden, error-prone, doesn't scale\n- **Decision**: Automated controller is chosen for reliability and scalability\n\n### 2. Kubernetes Garbage Collector with TTL\n- **Pros**: Built-in mechanism, no custom code\n- **Cons**: Requires adding TTL annotations to resources at creation time, can't track complex idle conditions\n- **Decision**: Custom controller provides more sophisticated idle detection logic\n\n### 3. External Cron Job\n- **Pros**: Simple implementation, decoupled from agentd\n- **Cons**: No real-time monitoring, can miss short-lived resources, duplicate leader election concerns\n- **Decision**: Integrated controller provides better event-driven response and consistent architecture\n\n### 4. OPA/Gatekeeper Policy\n- **Pros**: Centralized policy enforcement, validation-time checks\n- **Cons**: No ongoing monitoring/reconciliation, requires OPA infrastructure\n- **Decision**: Native Go controller is lighter and more maintainable for this use case\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n- Use `client-go` informers for efficient event-based monitoring of AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n- Implement finalizer-based deletion for clean removal\n- Leverage existing agentd controller scaffolding and leader election\n- Default idle timeout: 30 minutes for AgentRuntime, 15 minutes for CodeInterpreter\n- Dry-run mode enabled by default for safe rollout\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n1. **Unit Tests**: Test idle detection predicates and timeout calculations\n2. **Fake Client Tests**: Verify reconciliation logic with fake clientset\n3. **Integration Tests**: Test full controller lifecycle with minikube\n4. **Chaos Tests**: Simulate various idle states and edge cases","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775861619801,"end":1775861619805}}}}
